Wash and dry produce.

Drain @corn{1%unit}, then pat dry with #paper towels{}. Quarter @lime{1%unit}.

Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1%head}; cut into bite-size pieces. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Pat @ground turkey{10%ounce} dry with paper towels. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add turkey; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring frequently, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add corn and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and lightly charred in spots, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse @black beans{1%unit}. Once corn is lightly charred, add drained beans, half the @fajita spice blend{1%tbsp}, and a pinch of salt and pepper to pan; cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture is warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

> Use pan used for turkey here.

== Creamy Lime Dressing ==

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{}, whisk together @vegan mayo{2%tbsp}, juice from half the lime (juice from whole lime for 4 servings), a pinch of salt and pepper, and as much remaining Fajita Spice Blend as you like.

Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a dressing-like consistency (we used 2 tsp; 4 tsp for 4).

Add lettuce and cilantro to bowl with dressing and toss until thoroughly coated.

== Assembly ==

Divide salad between #bowls{}; top with corn and bean mixture and @pico de gallo{4%ounce}. Crumble as many @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%ounce} as you like on top and serve with any remaining lime wedges.

Top salad with turkey along with corn and bean mixture.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.